The paper discusses learning sparsifying transforms for signal processing and imaging applications, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the focus on sparsity suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) categories. The use of image data and denoising further suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Finally, the proposal of efficient learning algorithms and the consideration of multi-layer models suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
